text: Hillary event at Broward College flops, three squirrels and a pigeon show up! User Name Current Events Current Events Forum - Latest political news and events 1 Thanks SEE: Hillary Clinton to visit South Florida DAVIE, Fla. (WSVN) -- Democratic presidential frontrunner Hillary Clinton is expected to visit Broward College's Davie campus, Friday. She is scheduled to speak at a grassroots organizing meeting at the B. George Mayer Gymnasium. More than 2,000 supporters are expected to be in attendance. Unlike recent events held by the democratic hopeful, which have talked about specific subjects such as women's rights and the Cuban embargo, this meeting will a broad event aiming to drum up more support for her campaign. No one has been showing up! ItÂ’s time for Hilary to pack up her dog and pony show and leave! JWK
